<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-010-019 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 495 028</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  Nov 18 1991 v25 n46 p6(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Apple to offer guidance on client/server systems. (firm to releaseinternal documentation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Daly, James.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Apple plans to release an overview of an important internaldocument in Jan 1992 to help Apple Macintosh microcomputer userswho are creating client/server systems.andP;  The document, 'Vital,'summarizes the overall experience of Apple integrators.andP;  It hasbeen in use within Apple for a number of years.andP;  The document ismade up of various architectural guides that show how to integratea Mac into a client/server system in numerous differentenvironments.andP;  A more detailed version of Vital is planned forlater in 1992.andP;  Users applaud Apple's decision to release Vitalbecause they believe the document will help them better comprehendthe software and hardware connected with the client/serverapproach.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Apple Computer Inc. (Management).andO;Ticker:    AAPL.andO;Product:   Apple Macintosh (Microcomputer) (Usage).andO;Topic:     DocumentationCustomer RelationsSupport ServicesClient/server architectureUser NeedsGuidelinesSystem Development.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>